arts.ttl: Luxembourg vs. Germany: FIFA World Cup 2026 qualifier LIVE blog and team news
arts.sum: Anything other than maximum points from campaign-ending games in Luxembourg and at home to Slovakia (17 November), however, puts them at risk of going into the 16-team European play-offs, so Germany head coach Julian Nagelsmann will take no chances against a pointless Luxembourg side who were beaten 4-0 in the reverse fixture. The recalled Leroy Sané (Galatasaray) is a proven alternative in attack, while Nagelsmann has rewarded Cologne teenager Saïd El Mala for some electric performances at club level with a maiden senior call-up, along with Leipzig talent Assan Ouédraogo (a late replacement for the injured Nadiem Amiri ).

arts.ttl: Official | Joshua Kimmich to miss Germany’s Luxembourg clash, Ridle Baku to receive big chance?
arts.sum: The German FA has confirmed that Joshua Kimmich will miss out on tomorrow's FIFA World Cup qualification match against Luxembourg. The captain's absence - in all likelihood - translates to a huge opportunity for DFB returnee Ridle Baku.

arts.ttl: Joshua Kimmich to miss Luxembourg game after suffering injury in Germany training
